result.name: Golden City Seafood Restaurant

reviews.text: Very rude staff and dirty. We complained about a disgusting food stain on a plate and she took it away with a horrible attitude as if we were wrong to complain! It gets worst...she then puts it on a nearby table, ready for another customer to enjoy. Tasty. And we saw the customers sat down on that table 10mins later and they were also shocked at the disgusting food stain haha.

Came here for Sunday dinner. Ordered food at 7:11pm. Waited 50 mins for fried tofu. Another 15 mins for 2nd dish. Food was okay but it was not acceptable for such long wait for food. Do yourselves a favor, go somewhere else for dinner.
Good quality food for the price; wide variety of food and lots of space for large parties (12+). Careful of queues though; you might be waiting a while on (weekend) mornings.

During the CNY holiday, it's not that easy to get a table for dim sum as most Chinese would go to restaurants with their parents and elders to celebrate the festival. Have queued up for about 20 mins to get the table. Ordered some traditional dim sum and the most value-for-money one is the roasted duck with soup rice noodles, the taste was not bad but it was just Luke warm, making it much less tasty. Hope it would better next time. Other dim sum was so-so.
Don’t go there unless you want to enjoy Chinese style of service. Staffs are noisy and negative, impolite and irrespecutful. Know nothing of customer service.

reviews.text: A very good place for dining with midium price cuisine like roasted goose, Alaska crab and Cantonese fine soup. On site booking / waiting is required.
Good us okay and price is reasonable.

Good, high quality (albeit expensive) place to dine. Have been in small parties of 2 to over 10. When you arrive at the establishment (at the top of the escalators), you can choose how many seats you want and if you're willing to share a table. You'll then get a ticket with a letter and number, which is your queue for a table. Has cheap deals in the morning (before 11am) and a wide variety of Asian dishes (vegetarian, vegan, pork, chicken, duck etc). I will add pictures at a later date.
Price good,  food not bad.  A good place for big gathering

A great place for getting a real Hong Kong, Yum Cha experience. Delicious Dim Sum even though a tad on the pricey side.

Expect to wait 15-30min if going during peak times with a party more than 3-4 people.

Fairly noisey as to be expected from a Yum Cha house, with the ambient sound of the elderly Hong Kong locals speaking in Cantonese.

Unsure whether or not they have an English menu but they most likely do upon request. The ordering system is a tick and adding a number inside a box next to the desired product on sheets of paper and handing it to the staff walking around the area.

reviews.text: 點心新鮮味道👍😋😋😋😋
是一間燒腊出名的酒楼,早上有茶市,点心好食,晚飯消費取價公道.
这店在上水是原村民的最佳飯堂。我自己试过，确实当地高水凖的食府之一。缺点太多人捧场，輪侯時间長。😅
人多等候時間久.食物接受.水客佔多。

result.name: 金都海鮮酒家

reviews.text: ⚪k啦。
晚餐在此吃到四斤十一両的黄帝蠏很好。但小乳豬全體，肉少肥油膏多。吃例牌燒腩比較好。瑤柱蛋白炒飯不錯。價格不算貴，環境也可以接受。早茶每人五十元左右。午餐有特價乳鸽非常好吃又抵食。路過不要錯過。
出品比前進步，特價品也多，服務已有改善，座位也舒適，找位容易💪👍
食物味道很一般，看見服務員和客人吵架
